      "description": "The Department of Energy ARPA-E seeks proposals for the development of an advanced AI/ML platform for energy data analytics. The platform must support large-scale data processing, real-time analytics, predictive modeling, and visualization of energy grid data. Key requirements include: distributed computing architecture, support for TensorFlow and PyTorch frameworks, integration with existing DOE data systems, advanced security controls for sensitive energy infrastructure data, and scalable deployment across cloud and on-premises environments. Contract type: Firm Fixed Price. NAICS: 541519 - Other Computer Related Services. No set-aside restrictions. Estimated value: $5M-$8M over 3 years.",
